===Etymology===
{{bor|en|fr|mayonnaise}}, possibly named after the city {{w|Mahón}} whence the recipe was brought back to France. Alternative suggested origins include the city of Bayonne (bayonnaise); the French word {{m|fr|manier||to handle}}; the {{cog|fro|moyeu||egg yolk}}; and the Duke of Mayenne.

The United States {{w|standard of identity}} comes from [http://edocket.access.gpo.gov/cfr_2002/aprqtr/21cfr169.140.htm 21&nbsp;CFR 169.140].

